    <fr:title text="Threads on the hardware level">Threads on the hardware level</fr:title>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>I have been wondering how multithreading is actually implemented on the hardware level. Here, I summarize my findings:
<html:ul><html:li>Threads have their own program counter and can fetch and decode instructions in parallel.</html:li>
    <html:li>Threads have their own registers, but <html:strong>share</html:strong> most execution resources i.e. memory, ALU, etc.</html:li>
    <html:li>Thread instructions are scheduled just as typical instructions to maximize throughput.</html:li></html:ul></html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
